@namespace PgmStudio.Client.Pages.AuthoringParts

<section class="ds-section" id="flow">
  <div class="ds-section-heading">
    <div>
      <p class="ds-kicker">The flow</p>
      <h2>Six phases, one gate — define each thing once</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Dead-simple and guided: identity and world come first, each step shapes one slice of intent,
       and a playability gate closes the loop before export.</p>
  </div>

  <article class="ds-example">
    <div class="ds-example-label">Authoring pipeline — world seeds it, traversability gates it</div>
    <div class="ds-panel-frame">
      <div class="workspace-scroll">
        <section class="panel-section">
          <div class="section-header section-header--ruled">
            <h2 class="section-title">Phases</h2>
            <span class="badge badge--dim">thunder_blank</span>
          </div>
          <div class="section-body">
            <div class="step-row">
              <span class="step-dot step-dot--done"></span>
              <span class="step-label">0 · Map Info</span>
              <span class="step-detail">The basics the generator needs — map name and authors. Version, mode, objective auto-derived.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="step-row">
              <span class="step-dot step-dot--done"></span>
              <span class="step-label">1 · World</span>
              <span class="step-detail">Scan · Islands · Symmetry — detect the terrain as neutral shapes. Seeds team count and spawn positions.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="step-row">
              <span class="step-dot"></span>
              <span class="step-label">2 · Teams</span>
              <span class="step-detail">Team creation + island assignment, then spawn point + protection — defined once, orbit fills the rest.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="step-row">
              <span class="step-dot"></span>
              <span class="step-label">3 · Build</span>
              <span class="step-detail">Build height (side view) then the buildable layer of over-void bridges. The terrain is already buildable.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="step-row">
              <span class="step-dot"></span>
              <span class="step-label">4 · Wools</span>
              <span class="step-detail">Colours, then spawn + room, then monuments — one sub-step at a time; orbit fills the rest; rules auto-wired.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="step-row">
              <span class="step-dot step-dot--running"></span>
              <span class="step-label">5 · Review</span>
              <span class="step-detail">Round-trip · mirror-consistency · buildability · traversability gate — then export the XML.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="section-footer section-footer--separated">
            <div class="panel-warning">
              <strong>Build ⇄ Traversability is a loop.</strong> The closing gate is computed over the
              build / bridge geometry, so <em>build must precede wools</em>. If a spawn can't reach a wool,
              the gate sends you back to Build to add a bridge — it is not a separate step, it is the
              condition for export.
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</section>
